review_blob: Another great beer from Liberty. Lived up to its reputation. Good work Liberty.
Wow what a smooth, quality strong ale! superb aroma, soft bitter taste and sits perfectly on the palata lingering. Good work Panhead!
Great work again 8 Wired. Crisp, fresh hoppy IPA that goes down a treat. Excellent beer.

What a disappointment! Being a Hawkes Bay local I was expecting good things from this "handcrafted beer". It wasnt even on par with plain old boxed beer. I tried 4x 500ml varieties and same result, very reminiscent of my first or second batches of just acceptable home brew. Come on HBIB you can do better than this!

great IPA, hoppy aroma, quality appearance and very satisfying taste with mellow aftertaste. Nice work Bach Brewing, Ill have to try more in your range...
excellent double IPA, unbelievably smooth for a strong beer. well done again 8 Wired.
Very average beer, have been working my way through kiwi craft beers and this was disappointing, no better than a normal batch beer.
beer_name: Monteiths Brewers Series American Pale Ale

review_blob: Crisp, fresh and smooth APA, soft aftertaste. Excellent kiwi craft beer, well done Tuatara.
Well built stout. surprisingly smooth for a super strong stout beer, well done 8 wired, true kiwi ingenuity!
Exactly what youd expect from a kiwi style belgian tripel; clear, smooth beer with a fruity finish, in my opinion better than the belgian equivalents.

This beer is crazy, its like two drinks in one. the initial taste versus what rests on your palate a second or two later is black versus white. Amazing job Tuatara, an inspiration to any home brewer who is after something special.
Great double IPA! This beer is smooth, balanced and relatively soft on the palate. A truly excellent beer, thanks Liberty!
Excellent IPA. well priced IPA that is fresh, crisp, nice on the palate and very smooth. Well done EPIC.

Working my way through kiwi craft beers and this is the first that isnt worthy of being kiwi, comparable to the cheap Atlas or Pirate Beer that they sell at Countdown, disappointing given its the most expensive kiwi craft at $11/330ml.
beer_name: Yeastie Boys The Sun Before the Darkness
